title: For Sale:  Remington R1 enhanced 1911 threaded barrel
postcontent:
This is an Advanced Armament Corp 1911. The gun is a Remington R1 Enhanced that has been tuned and customized by Advanced Armament Corp (who makes some of the best silencers in the world). The slide has advanced armament branding, and has their skull and cross guns symbol laser engraved on the side. The grips are special edition AAC G10 Hogue, with the frag texture. This pistol is optimized for use with silencers. It comes with a threaded barrel and tall sights that extend above the silencer. This is one of the most accurate and reliable pistols I've ever shot. This one has just barely been broken in with about 350 rounds through it, not a single malfunction. 
This pistol comes with two 8 round magazines. I do not have a box, but I have a zippered padded pouch I'll throw in. 
 
 
Must have a valid tn driver's license and be legally able to own a firearms. Handgun carry permit holders preferred. Must be willing to fill out a bill of sale. I've bought and sold on here alot. This is a great gun. If you are serious, I'd be happy to meet at a range like OnTarget and let you see for yourself. You won't be disappointed. Please feel free to contact me with any questions whatsoever. Thanks for looking!
I am NOT interested in any trades. 
 
To cover all the features, here's an excerpt from a review of this gun from tactical-Life.Com:
 
"To set the R1 Enhanced Threaded Barrel apart from its siblings, it sports several refinements. The first differences you’ll notice when handling the pistol are the extra-high front and rear sights. These sights are well built and capable of maintaining their zero with hard use. The sights are set up in a two-stacked-dot configuration for fast targeting.

Also differing from a run-of-the-mill 1911 are the pistol’s front and rear slide serrations. These square-cut serrations have a forward slant that roughly matches the pistol’s grip angle. Care taken in the finishing process to not round off the edges of the broad serrations gives them a bold look and full functionality. The rear portion of the ejection port also has had some metal relieved to improve ejection, and a small port on top that, when viewed from above, allows shooters to see if the chambered is loaded.The grip safety is enhanced with a beavertail extension, and it has the nice added feature of what Remington calls a “checkered memory bump” that maintains the same 20-lines-per-inch (lpi) checkering on the mainspring housing. The frontstrap is serrated, and the wood laminate grip panels are checkered. The left-side panel features a thumb groove for a right-handed shooter. The R1 Enhanced Threaded Barrel pistol also has a beveled magazine well for fast reloads, and it comes from the factory with two 8-round magazines fitted with bumper pads.
The anodized aluminum, match trigger is the extended type, and it’s also skeletonized to reduce weight. From the factory, the trigger breaks at 3.5 pounds with a small amount of creep and overtravel. The thumb safety is upgraded with a little more length and width, and it functions well for those with larger hands. The pistol also features a lightweight, skeletonized hammer.
At the heart of every good pistol is a good barrel, and the R1 Enhanced Threaded Barrel features a match-grade, stainless steel barrel that is 5 inches long. It’s held in place with a stainless steel bushing. Again, the barrel is threaded, and it comes with a thread protector.

The fit and finish of the R1 Enhanced Threaded Barrel is on par with many custom Model 1911s I’ve tested. 
 
The R1 Enhanced Threaded Barrel boasts enough upgrades to satisfy most shooters, and the capability to attach suppressors promises quiet, fun shooting. Its accuracy is noteworthy, and it’s certainly worth the $1,140 price tag."
